<p><strong><em>Getting Started with GitHub</em></strong></p>

<p>GitHub is an excellent way to collaborate with your team while working on a code.
First step is to register you user name and create a password.
Open <a href="http://www.github.com" title="GitHub Website">GitHub Website</a> and create a new account. The account is free and allows users to create multiple blogs.
<strong>Repository</strong>is created to keep your projects organized.</p>

<p>GitHub blogs can be maintained and modified directly by editing the code in your</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>_post
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>or by editing the code locally and then pushing it to <strong>Github</strong> with <em>Jekyll</em>.</p>

